main event: An individual reported unidentified sounds resembling foreign type aircraft motors in Baltimore, Maryland on 23 March 1948.
interesting points: The report indicates that the observer wished to keep her identity confidential,The observer was active in American Legion activities and used to discuss her findings with others,There were no identifiable visual sightings of the objects, but sounds were noted during specific hours,The account includes mentions of similar sound reports from a neighbor,The reporting individual emphasized she was not hysterical nor unduly apprehensive.
witness description: an anonymous civilian and a neighbor
